content: Excellent, thank you! Now we're getting somewhere. So yes, I have a question. The yellow warning light came on my klargen this morning on the way to work. I believe it was due to low coolant. So I removed the tungsten alloy cover and checked the tank; it was empty and the coolant had sprayed all over my troporigniants. It looked like the creantimeal cap was not turn on correctly or something. Could it be that I shanked the wik so it blew the cap or that it just sprayed out from the bleev-valve?
